{"id":"belly","term":"Belly","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>The seat of the carnal affections (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Titus 1:12\">Titus 1:12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Philippians 3:19\">Phil. 3:19</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Romans 16:18\">Rom. 16:18</a>). The word is used symbolically for the heart (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 18:8\">Prov. 18:8</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 20:27\">20:27</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Proverbs 22:18\">22:18</a>, marg.). The “belly of hell” signifies the grave or underworld (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Jonah 2:2\">Jonah 2:2</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Titus 1:12","Philippians 3:19","Romans 16:18","Proverbs 18:8","Proverbs 20:27","Proverbs 22:18","Jonah 2:2"]}